
TY  - JOUR
T1  - Transformational Leadership's Role in Promoting Corporate Entrepreneurship: Examining the CEO-TMT Interface
AU  - Ling, Yan
AU  - Simsek, Zeki
AU  - Lubatkin, Michael H.
AU  - Veiga, John F.
Y1  - 2008/06/01
PY  - 2008
DA  - 2008/06/01
N1  - doi: 10.5465/amj.2008.32626023
DO  - 10.5465/amj.2008.32626023
T2  - Academy of Management Journal
JF  - Academy of Management Journal
JO  - AMJ
SP  - 557
EP  - 576
VL  - 51
IS  - 3
PB  - Academy of Management
N2  - Research about transformational CEOs' impact on firm-level outcomes, particularly corporate entrepreneurship, has been equivocal, partially because the underlying mechanisms remain largely unexplored. Given that the individuals most closely influenced by a firm's CEO are its top management team (TMT) members, we focus on the CEO-TMT interface as a salient intervening mechanism. We posit that transformational CEOs influence TMTs' behavioral integration, risk propensity, decentralization of responsibilities, and long-term compensation and that these TMT characteristics impact corporate entrepreneurship. Data from 152 firms supported most of our hypothesized links, underscoring how the CEO-TMT interface helps explain transformational CEOs' role in promoting corporate entrepreneurship.
AB  - Research about transformational CEOs' impact on firm-level outcomes, particularly corporate entrepreneurship, has been equivocal, partially because the underlying mechanisms remain largely unexplored. Given that the individuals most closely influenced by a firm's CEO are its top management team (TMT) members, we focus on the CEO-TMT interface as a salient intervening mechanism. We posit that transformational CEOs influence TMTs' behavioral integration, risk propensity, decentralization of responsibilities, and long-term compensation and that these TMT characteristics impact corporate entrepreneurship. Data from 152 firms supported most of our hypothesized links, underscoring how the CEO-TMT interface helps explain transformational CEOs' role in promoting corporate entrepreneurship.
